&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 4), i.e., Lackadaisical.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-37b9a022-7fff-aad1-44cd-c5ca1d4f354c&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border: none; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 164px; height: 44px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/Cu-Fh9F0AzduobRK0iOmxJZRQNYNzr0sIeWjMwBPW6nR0uOWP2-WxoPBTtRRGtNBvFJXdHKyngPFpsCo3kfRzYZpqjuGbuaAotK34V_crtcDdmC8H8ZWEhsPto-S1oJd5ii6fsHQ&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px; width: 164px; height: 44px; float: left;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
If you say that someone is &lt;strong&gt;lackadaisical&lt;/strong&gt;, you mean that they are rather&lt;strong&gt; lazy and do not show much interest or enthusiasm in what they do.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;E.g.: I hope the medicine is not causing you to be sleepy and &lt;strong&gt;lackadaisical.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 4&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Pitch and toss&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to &lt;strong&gt;a game of chance&lt;/strong&gt;. (भाग्य का खेल)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;Investing in the stock market can sometimes feel like a &lt;strong&gt;pitch and toss,&lt;/strong&gt; where outcomes are uncertain.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Pitch and toss&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is used to describe situations where outcomes are highly unpredictable and reliant on luck. (भाग्य पर निर्भरता)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;Life is often a &lt;strong&gt;pitch and toss&lt;/strong&gt;, and we must be prepared for anything that comes our way.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To feel unlucky&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;दुर्भाग्य महसूस करना&lt;/span&gt;): To experience a sense of misfortune.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; After missing the bus, he felt very unlucky.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To reveal a secret&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;राज़ खोलना&lt;/span&gt;): To disclose confidential information.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She accidentally revealed the secret about the surprise party.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A brief account of something&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;संक्षिप्त विवरण&lt;/span&gt;): A short summary or description.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The professor gave a brief account of the history of the Roman Empire.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Disagree&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Concur&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; means&amp;nbsp;to have or come to the same opinion or point of view.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;antonyms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the word&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Concur&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;disagree, differ, dissociate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonym&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given word, we can say that the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Disagree&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;opposite&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;in&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;meaning&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Disagree&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;have or express a different opinion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hence&lt;/span&gt;, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 3&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;Let&amp;#39;s see the meaning of other given options-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;WORDS&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;MEANING&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Contribute&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;give something in order to help achieve or provide something&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Lead&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;organize and direct&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Distribute&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;spread over an area.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;synonyms&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the word&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Concur&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;assemble, converge, gather&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Example&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;of&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Concur&lt;/u&gt;&lt;u&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;in a&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&amp;nbsp;sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Actually, much research and many experts &lt;strong&gt;concur&lt;/strong&gt; with both points.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Fidelity&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Deception&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;means&amp;nbsp;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;making somebody believe or being made to believe something that is not true (&lt;strong&gt;धोखा देने की क्रिया&lt;/strong&gt;)&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Dilip admitted conspiring to obtain property by&lt;strong&gt; deception.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Marked option&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Fidelity&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;means&amp;nbsp;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;faithfulness to a person, cause, or belief, demonstrated by continuing loyalty and support (&lt;strong&gt;किसी व्यक्ति, कारण या विश्वास के प्रति वफादारी, निरंतर वफादारी और समर्थन द्वारा प्रदर्शित&lt;/strong&gt;)&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Customer trust and &lt;strong&gt;fidelity &lt;/strong&gt;are not acquired once and for all.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Fidelity&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;best&amp;nbsp;expresses the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;opposite&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;meaning as the given word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Deception&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;correct answer&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Chicanery&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;dishonest but attractive talk or behavior that is used to deceive people (&lt;strong&gt;बेईमान लेकिन आकर्षक बात या व्यवहार जो लोगों को धोखा देने के लिए प्रयोग किया जाता है&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hoax&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;means a trick to make people believe something that is not true, especially something unpleasant (&lt;strong&gt;कुछ असत्&amp;zwj;य को सत्&amp;zwj;य दर्शाने के लिए किया गया छल प्रायः बुरा, झाँसा&amp;nbsp;देना&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Pretence&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;an action that makes people believe something that is not true (&lt;strong&gt;प्रदर्शन, ढोंग, दिखावा&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;pusillanimous&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given word&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39; Timorous&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means&amp;nbsp;showing or suffering from nervousness or a lack of confidence.(घबराहट)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The sound of a wolf&amp;#39;s growling howl at night in the jungle made the tourists &lt;strong&gt;timorous.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The marked option&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;pusillanimous&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; means&amp;nbsp;showing a lack of courage or determination; timid.(कमज़ोर दिलवाला).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the given meanings of both these words, we can say that &amp;#39;pusillanimous&amp;#39; is nearest in meaning to&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;timorous&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 4.&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Audacious &lt;/strong&gt;means&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;willing to take risks or do something shocking(&amp;nbsp;ख़तरा उठाने या स्&amp;zwj;तब्&amp;zwj;धकारी कार्य करने को तैयार; निर्भीक, निडर)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supercilious &lt;/strong&gt;means&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;showing that you think that you are better than other people.(दंभी, मग़रूर, अवमानी)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Factual&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Fictitious&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is an adjective&amp;nbsp;that means&amp;nbsp;not real or true; imaginary or fabricated.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the given options are as follows -&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;False&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;not according to truth or fact; incorrect (असत्&amp;zwj;य, ग़लत).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Factual&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;concerned with what is actually the case (तथ्&amp;zwj;यों पर आधारित).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Imaginative&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;having or showing creativity or inventiveness (कल्&amp;zwj;पना से उत्&amp;zwj;पन्&amp;zwj;न, कल्&amp;zwj;पनाशील).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subjective&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;based on or influenced by personal feelings, tastes, or opinions ((तथ्&amp;zwj;यों के स्&amp;zwj;थान पर) निजी रुचियों और विचारों पर आधारित).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the above meanings, it is evident that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;factual&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct antonym for the word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;fictitious&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct answer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

